step.by: submitted by the Chair of the Committee following informal consultations

p.docTitle: Resolutions adopted by the General Assembly on 30 December 2022

p.docProponent: [on the report of the Fifth Committee (A/77/672, para. 68)]

content.p: Appropriations totalling 3,396,308,300 United States dollars are hereby approved for the following purposes:

td.p: Part I. Overall policymaking, direction and coordination
General Assembly and Economic and Social Council affairs and conference management
Part III. International justice and law
Part IV. International cooperation for development
Least developed countries, landlocked developing countries and small island developing States
United Nations system support for the African Union’s Agenda 2063: The Africa We Want
International drug control, crime and terrorism prevention and criminal justice
Part V. Regional cooperation for development
Economic and social development in Africa
Economic and social development in Asia and the Pacific
Economic and social development in Latin America and the Caribbean
Economic and social development in Western Asia
Part VI. Human rights and humanitarian affairs
International protection, durable solutions and assistance to refugees
Department of Management Strategy, Policy and Compliance
Office of Information and Communications Technology
Part X. Jointly financed administrative activities and special expenses
Construction, alteration, improvement and major maintenance

content.p: In addition to the appropriations approved under paragraph 1 above, an amount of 75,000 dollars is appropriated for 2023 from the accumulated income of the Library Endowment Fund for the purchase of books, periodicals, maps and library equipment and for such other expenses of the Library at the Palais des Nations in Geneva as are in accordance with the objects and provisions of the endowment.
Estimates of income totalling 321,949,500 United States dollars are approved as follows:
The income from staff assessment shall be credited to the Tax Equalization Fund in accordance with the provisions of General Assembly resolution 973 (X) of 15 December 1955;

Direct expenses of the United Nations Postal Administration, services to visitors, the sale of statistical products, catering operations and related services, garage operations, television services and the sale of publications not provided for under the budget appropriations shall be charged against the income derived from those activities.

docTitle.span: Financing of appropriations for the year 2023

intro.p:
Budget appropriations totalling 3,443,427,800 United States dollars, consisting of 3,396,308,300 dollars approved for 2023 by the General Assembly in paragraph 1 of resolution A above, and 47,119,500 dollars in additional appropriations for 2022, as approved by the Assembly in its resolution 76/246 B of 13 April 2022, its decision 76/564 of 23 May 2022 and its resolution 76/271 of 29 June 2022, shall be financed in accordance with regulations 3.1 and 3.2 of the Financial Regulations and Rules of the United Nations,
ST/SGB/2013/4 and ST/SGB/2013/4/Amend.1. as follows:

content.p: 30,594,700 dollars, representing the estimated income other than staff assessment income approved for 2023 under resolution B above;

195,116,800 dollars, as reflected in the financial performance report on the programme budget for 2021,
A/77/347. approved by the Assembly in section VII of its resolution 77/263 of 30 December 2022;

3,217,716,300 dollars, representing the assessment on Member States in accordance with Assembly resolution 76/238 of 24 December 2021 on the scale of assessments for the apportionment of the expenses of the United Nations;

There shall be set off against the assessment on Member States, in accordance with the provisions of General Assembly resolution 973 (X) of 15 December 1955, their respective share in the Tax Equalization Fund totalling 292,390,400 dollars, consisting of 291,354,800 dollars related to the appropriations for 2023 and 1,035,600 dollars related to the additional appropriations for 2022, as approved by the Assembly in its resolution 76/246 B, its decision 76/564 and its resolution 76/271.
